RnB sensation Usher set the stage on fire at the Global Citizen Festival: Mandela 100  when he totally rocked popular Mzansi dance moves the vosho and gwara gwara. Thousands of fans have packed the FNB Stadium in Soweto to capacity for the highly anticipated international music festival with a cause. Usher's collab with DJ Black Coffee to We Dance Again had fans losing their minds. The US hitmaker who is known for his smooth vocals and smoking-hot dance moves burnt a hole in the stage and had the ladies eating out of the palm of his hands. It's not surprising that Usher quickly topped the Twitter trends list across Mzansi. Here's a glimpse of the heartthrob in action: The Twitter streets have been an absolute mess ever since Usher's rocking performance.